  "prompt": "How much does it cost to build a robot?",
  "response": "The cost of building a robot can vary widely depending on several factors, including:\n\n1. **Type of Robot**: \n   - Simple hobby robots (like basic Arduino or Raspberry Pi projects) can cost anywhere from $50 to a few hundred dollars.\n   - More complex robots (like industrial robots or robotic arms) can range from several thousand to hundreds of thousands of dollars.\n\n2. **Components**: \n   - Sensors, motors, microcontrollers, batteries, and other components can add up. Basic sensors might cost less than $10 each, while advanced sensors and actuators could cost hundreds.\n\n3. **Software**: \n   - If you are using proprietary software or advanced machine learning algorithms, the cost can increase significantly.\n\n4. **Design and Prototyping**: \n   - Custom components or advanced designs may require additional costs for materials and prototyping.\n\n5. **Labor**: \n   - The cost of labor (engineering time, assembly, programming) can significantly impact the total cost, especially for more advanced projects.\n\n6. **Research and Development**: \n   - If the robot is being developed for commercial purposes, R&D costs must be factored in.\n\n7. **Regulatory Compliance**: \n   - Costs associated with meeting regulations for safety and certification may apply, especially for commercial robots.\n\nIn summary, a basic hobby robot can start under $100, whereas a sophisticated robot for commercial use could easily exceed $100,000. Some advanced, specialized robots can even cost millions.",
